Organizers report an increasing number of bookings
This should be a good winter for German travel agencies:
In terms of bookings for the coming months according to a study, the turnover has increased significantly compared with the previous year - for the winter season, even by more than 30 percent.
Despite weak cyclical prospects, the thirst for German travel remains insatiable according to this study.
With regard to bookings for the winter season, travel agencies recorded a turnover of more than 31 per cent compared to the same period the previous year, as entrusted to Berlin on Monday by the German Federation of Travel Agencies (DRV).
According to the survey of the GfK Market Research Institute, increasing booking figures already dominate the fall months.
Thus the sales figure would have climbed to about 11 per cent in comparison with 2007, confided the RVD.
The sources of these results are the GfK figures, which analyses the bookings data of 1200 travel agencies on a monthly basis and makes estimates for the overall market.
Travel bookings made since the end of August 2008 would be recorded there.
Due to the low price of the dollar, travel to the US would be particularly requested, said the DRV.
There, the increase in bookings would amount to about one third.
Besides this, Spain, Turkey and Greece as well as our country would be particularly sought after by Germans.
Especially organized trips are very popular, explained the president of the DRV Klaus Laepple.
In view of the rising prices of energy and food products, the costs here would be "more easily calculable for the customer than for a trip organised individually".
Consumers can save money, among other things, with reductions in advance bookings or All Inclusive offers, Laepple explained.
The summer months have also been very successful so that an increase in sales figures will be recorded again compared to last year - although another study has shown that the number of Germans who undertook a trip has decreased compared with the previous year.
