Morgan Stanley announced the opening of Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group (MUFG), Japan's first bank, which will pay $9 billion to take 21% of its capital, a news received by a sharp drop in its stock market price.
One week after announcing a provisional agreement, the two banks explained that MUFG would purchase 9.9% of Morgan Stanley common shares at a unit price of $25.25, for a total amount of $3 billion.
